# Chrome Extension Build Log - 2026-05-07

## Requirements (User Prompts)

1. "I want to build a chrome extension, here is the requirements:"
2. "1. Based on local time, the chrome settings will be modified by itself, and installed extension will be turned on/off by itself. 2. settings include statup tabs 3. Extensions ID will be provided in the config of this new chrome extension."

## Implementation Summary

Built a Manifest V3 Chrome extension at: chrome-extension/

### Files Created
- manifest.json - Permissions: management, storage, alarms, tabs
- background.js - Service worker with time-based rule engine, alarm scheduling, extension toggling, startup tab handling
- options.html + options.js - Configuration UI for rules (time ranges, days, extension IDs, startup tabs)
- popup.html + popup.js - Status display showing active rule, next transition, extension states

### How It Works
- Rules define time ranges + days of week + extension IDs to enable/disable + startup tab URLs
- Alarm fires at each rule start/end boundary to re-evaluate active rule
- chrome.management.setEnabled() toggles extensions
- chrome.runtime.onStartup opens configured tabs
- Config stored in chrome.storage.local, changes detected via onChanged
